Applicants for new or renewed passports face an indefinite wait as the government does not have the foreign currency to pay for special imported paper, ink and other raw materials. 

Millions of Zimbabweans have fled abroad in the last 20 years seeking work as hyperinflation wiped out savings and the formal employment sector collapsed. 

Many others are now seeking to leave as conditions worsen under President Emmerson Mnangagwa, who had promised an economic revival after succeeding long-time leader Robert Mugabe in 2017. 

To discuss this further, Samora Mangesi spoke to Zimbabwean Political Analyst, Alexander Rusero, and started off by asking him how the situation is like currently in Zimbabwe... -ChannelAfrica--